{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[[]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/oudscomponents"]}],"topicSections":[{"title":"Group","identifiers":["doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton"],"anchor":"Group"},{"anchor":"Enumerations","title":"Enumerations","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/AccessibilityFocusable"]},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/SwiftUICore"],"title":"Extended Modules","generated":true,"anchor":"Extended-Modules"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Buttons","level":3,"text":"Buttons"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" propose layout with text only, icon only or text and icon."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Four hierarchies are proposed for all layouts: ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"default"}]},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"strong"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"minimal"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"negative"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Two style are available: "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"default","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"loading"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"If button is placed on colored surface using ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSColoredSurface","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", the default colors (content, background and border) are automatically adjusted to switch to monochrom.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"A button with ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSButton.Hierarchy.Negative","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" hierarchy is not allowed as a direct or indirect child of an "},{"code":"OUDSColoredSurface","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["     \/\/ Icon only with default hierarchy","     OUDSButton(hierarchy: .default, icon: Image(\"ic_heart\")) {}","","     \/\/ Text only with negative hierarchy","     OUDSButton(hierarchy: .negative, text: \"Delete\") {}","","     \/\/ Text and icon with strong hierarchy","     OUDSButton(hierarchy: .strong, icon: Image(\"ic_heart\"), text: \"Validate\") {}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Customize-components","text":"Customize components","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"text":"Apply a specific shadow effect (elevation tokens)","anchor":"Apply-a-specific-shadow-effect-elevation-tokens","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The unified design system implemented by OUDS iOS library allows to apply ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"elevation effets"}]},{"type":"text","text":" on a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"View"},{"text":", i.e. a shadow under the component.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Because the design tool in use is "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Figma"}]},{"text":" which defines such shadow with a ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"blur","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" and a "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"spread"}]},{"type":"text","text":" radiuses, and because "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"SwiftUI"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" uses only its own "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"radius","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" definition, an extension of "},{"code":"View","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" has been implemented to let users apply some effect using an ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudstokenssemantic\/elevationcompositesemantictoken","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" from the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudstokenssemantic\/"},{"text":" library thanks to the method ","type":"text"},{"code":"shadow(elevation: ElevationCompositeSemanticToken)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"code":["\/\/ For example, apply the elevation effect \"elevationDragLight\" from your theme:","myView.shadow(elevation: theme.elevationDragLight)","","\/\/ And in the theme this \"elevationDragLight\" has been defined for example like:","@objc open var elevationDragLight: ElevationCompositeSemanticToken { ElevationRawTokens.elevationBottom_3_500 }","ColorRawTokens.colorOpacityBlack400)","","\/\/ And if you look deeper, the raw token \"elevationBottom_3_500\" can be like:","public static let elevationBottom_3_500 = ElevationCompositeRawToken(x: 0, y: 4, blur: 4, color: ColorRawTokens.colorOpacityBlack500)","","\/\/ Blur will be used to compute the radius value"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Apply-a-specific-typography-font-tokens","text":"Apply a specific typography (font tokens)","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Your application identity can be strongly based on the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"typography","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" you use, i.e. the font family you choose and other configuration details like the font size or the font weight."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"With OUDS, typography depends to the class size, i.e. wether or not the application is in "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"compact mode"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" or in "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"regular mode","type":"text"}]},{"text":", and is defined with a ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudstokenssemantic\/multiplefontcompositerawtokens","type":"reference"},{"text":". defined in the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudstokenssemantic\/fontsemantictokens\/","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"theme"}]},{"text":" contains lots of ","type":"text"},{"code":"MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" listing all the combinations of typography you can apply, and these "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"composite semantic tokens","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" use "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"composite raw tokens"}]},{"type":"text","text":". For example:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Here is a definition of a semantic token inside the theme for typography \"typeDisplayMedium\":","@objc open var typeDisplayMedium: MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens { ","MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens(compact: FontRawTokens.typeBold750, regular: FontRawTokens.typeBold1050) ","}","","\/\/ And here are the raw tokebs definitions:","public static let typeBold750 = FontCompositeRawToken(size: fontSize750, lineHeight: fontLineHeight850, weight: fontWeightBold)","","public static let typeBold1050 = FontCompositeRawToken(size: fontSize1050, lineHeight: fontLineHeight1150, weight: fontWeightBold)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"However the ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"theme","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" must know which "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"font family","type":"text"}]},{"text":" to apply, and this font family can be a ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"custom one","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" or the ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"system one"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Thus, we let the users define the font family they want by overriding the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fontFamily"},{"type":"text","text":" property. This value will be used to compute the typography, if not defined the systme font will be used."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Thus, if you want to apply a specific typography to a ","type":"text"},{"code":"View","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", supposing you defined previously the semantic tokens, just call the method you want and gives as parameter the theme (to get the custom font if defined):"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["\/\/ Apply typography \"type body default small\"","myView.typeBodyDefaultSmall(theme)","","\/\/ Apply typography \"type label strong X large\"","myView.typeLabelStrongXLarge(theme)","","\/\/ Etc."],"syntax":"swift"},{"text":"Apply a specific border (border tokens)","anchor":"Apply-a-specific-border-border-tokens","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This module exposes the helper ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"oudsBorder(style:width:radius:color)"},{"text":" so as to apply border semantic tokens on a view in order to define a border effect.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"The helper is available through "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"View"},{"type":"text","text":", and tokens through the provider of the theme."}]},{"code":["    @Environment(\\.theme) private var theme","","    var body: some View {","        SomeView()","        .oudsBorder(","             style: theme.borders.borderStyleDefault,","             width: theme.borders.borderWidthThin,","             radius: theme.borders.borderRadiusNone,","             color: theme.colors.colorBorderDefault)","     }"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"}]}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"OUDSComponents"}],"role":"collection","title":"OUDSComponents","externalID":"OUDSComponents","roleHeading":"Framework","symbolKind":"module"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The catalog of all components provided by OUDS. It contains also "},{"code":"View","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" extensions and ","type":"text"},{"code":"ViewModifiers","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to apply tokens and styles on components and higher-level views.","type":"text"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"references":{"https://ios.unified-design-system.orange.com/documentation/oudstokenssemantic/multiplefontcompositerawtokens":{"identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudstokenssemantic\/multiplefontcompositerawtokens","titleInlineContent":[{"code":"MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens","type":"codeVoice"}],"url":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudstokenssemantic\/multiplefontcompositerawtokens","type":"link","title":"MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens"},"https://ios.unified-design-system.orange.com/documentation/oudstokenssemantic/":{"titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSTokensSemantic"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudstokenssemantic\/","url":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudstokenssemantic\/","type":"link","title":"OUDSTokensSemantic"},"https://ios.unified-design-system.orange.com/documentation/oudstokenssemantic/fontse